# Legacy OAuth client credentials reference for the Antigravity plugin.
#
# This file is documentation only. Do not copy it to
# antigravity_auth/_credentials.py and do not put real credentials in the
# package tree; package-tree credential files can leak into wheels/sdists and
# are refused by package builds.
#
# Put OAuth values in environment variables instead:
#   export ANTIGRAVITY_CLIENT_ID="your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com"
#   export ANTIGRAVITY_CLIENT_SECRET="your-client-secret"
#
# Or use the external Hermes credentials file outside the package tree:
#   ~/.hermes/antigravity-credentials.json
# with JSON keys:
#   {"client_id": "...", "client_secret": "..."}
#
# To get credentials:
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#   2. Create a "Desktop application" OAuth 2.0 client ID
#   3. Add http://localhost:51121/oauth-callback as an authorized redirect URI
#   4. Copy the client ID and secret into the environment variables or
#      ~/.hermes/antigravity-credentials.json described above.
#
# No Python assignments are provided here intentionally: this example is a
# nonfunctional legacy reference, not a credentials template to fill in.
